#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/dev/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/bundle-dynamic-imports.md
M|rules|title: Dynamic Imports for Heavy Components
M|rules|impact: CRITICAL
M|rules|impactDescription: directly affects TTI and LCP
M|rules|tags: bundle, dynamic-import, code-splitting, next-dynamic
M|rules|Use `next/dynamic` to lazy-load large components not needed on initial render.
M|rules|**Incorrect (Monaco bundles with main chunk ~300KB):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|import { MonacoEditor } from './monaco-editor'
M|rules|function CodePanel({ code }: { code: string }) {
M|rules|return <MonacoEditor value={code} />
M|rules|}
M|rules|```
M|rules|**Correct (Monaco loads on demand):**
M|rules|```tsx
M|rules|import dynamic from 'next/dynamic'
M|rules|const MonacoEditor = dynamic(
M|rules|() => import('./monaco-editor').then(m => m.MonacoEditor),
M|rules|{ ssr: false }
M|rules|)
M|rules|function CodePanel({ code }: { code: string }) {
M|rules|return <MonacoEditor value={code} />
M|rules|}
M|rules|```